cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with object instance re-identification using visual features and proposes an extension to the Mask R-CNN architecture. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper involves learning and encoding information from the background to aid in the object re-identification task. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper involves training a model to jointly learn foreground and background features. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as the paper deals with re-identification of objects in a rigid environment, which could be relevant to robotics applications. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with visual features and object re-identification, which could be relevant to multimedia applications.
